## Problem
The `/brands` hub (priority 0.9) and 8 individual brand landing pages at `/brands/<slug>` (priority 0.8) are declared in `api/sitemap.js` but have **zero handler** in `api/meta/[...path].js`. All 9 pages serve the generic fallback.

**Verified:** `grep -n "'/brands'\|path.*brands\/" api/meta/[...path].js` → only two hits for a helper function (lines 144/151), no page-level handler.

**⚠️ DISTINCT FROM #1383** (Gear brand pages `/gear/<brand>`). These `/brands/<slug>` pages are brand info/landing pages, not gear-category views.

Brand slugs from `api/sitemap.js` `gearBrands` array: `tama`, `pearl`, `dw`, `ludwig`, `zildjian`, `paiste`, `meinl`, `sabian`.

**Same bug class as:** #1172 (/bands hub + /bands/<slug>, shipped), #1383 (/gear/<brand>, approved).

## Fix
**File:** `api/meta/[...path].js` — add after the `/bands` section:

```javascript
// /brands hub
if (path === '/brands') {
  return {
    title: `Metal Drum & Cymbal Brands Used by Pro Drummers | ${SITE_NAME}`,
    description: 'Browse drum and cymbal brands used by 60+ metal legends. Tama, Pearl, DW, Zildjian, Paiste, Meinl, Sabian — see which pros endorse each brand.',
    image: DEFAULT_IMAGE,
    type: 'website',
    url: `${BASE_URL}/brands`,
    breadcrumbSchema: [
      { name: 'Home', url: BASE_URL },
      { name: 'Gear Brands', url: `${BASE_URL}/brands` },
    ],
  };
}

// /brands/<slug> individual brand pages
const BRAND_META = {
  tama: { name: 'Tama', type: 'drums' },
  pearl: { name: 'Pearl', type: 'drums' },
  dw: { name: 'DW (Drum Workshop)', type: 'drums' },
  ludwig: { name: 'Ludwig', type: 'drums' },
  zildjian: { name: 'Zildjian', type: 'cymbals' },
  paiste: { name: 'Paiste', type: 'cymbals' },
  meinl: { name: 'Meinl', type: 'cymbals' },
  sabian: { name: 'Sabian', type: 'cymbals' },
};
const brandPageMatch = path.match(/^\/brands\/([a-z0-9-]+)$/);
if (brandPageMatch) {
  const brand = BRAND_META[brandPageMatch[1]];
  if (brand) {
    return {
      title: `${brand.name} Drums — Metal Drummers Who Use ${brand.name} | ${SITE_NAME}`,
      description: `Which metal drummers use ${brand.name} ${brand.type}? See every pro in MetalForge's database who endorses or plays ${brand.name} gear — kit specs and prices.`,
      image: DEFAULT_IMAGE,
      type: 'website',
      url: `${BASE_URL}/brands/${brandPageMatch[1]}`,
      breadcrumbSchema: [
        { name: 'Home', url: BASE_URL },
        { name: 'Gear Brands', url: `${BASE_URL}/brands` },
        { name: brand.name, url: `${BASE_URL}/brands/${brandPageMatch[1]}` },
      ],
    };
  }
}
```

## Estimated organic uplift
Enables keyword-matched SERP snippets for purchase-intent brand queries: "tama metal drummers", "who uses zildjian cymbals", "paiste metal". These are buyer-journey queries with strong affiliate conversion potential.

## Verify
1. `curl -s -A 'Googlebot' 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/brands'` → title contains "Brands"
2. `curl -s -A 'Googlebot' 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/brands/tama'` → title contains "Tama"
3. `curl -s -A 'Googlebot' 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/brands/zildjian'` → title contains "Zildjian"
4. BreadcrumbList schema present in response for individual brand pages
5. No generic fallback on any `/brands` or `/brands/<slug>` page

## Done
`/brands` hub and all 8 `/brands/<slug>` pages return keyword-matched meta + BreadcrumbList from `api/meta/[...path].js`.
